75static const char iMajorError[] = "invalid major number";
76static const char iMinorError[] = "invalid minor number";
77static const char tooManyFields[] = "too many fields for format";
78
79/* This is blatantly stolen from libarchive/archive_entry.c,
80 * in an attempt to get this to play nice on MinGW... */
81#if !defined(HAVE_MAJOR) && !defined(major)
82/* Replacement for major/minor/makedev. */
83#define major(x) ((int)(0x00ff & ((x) >> 8)))
84#define minor(x) ((int)(0xffff00ff & (x)))
85#define makedev(maj,min) ((0xff00 & ((maj)<<8)) | (0xffff00ff & (min)))
86#endif
87
88/* Play games to come up with a suitable makedev() definition. */
89#ifdef __QNXNTO__
90/* QNX. <sigh> */
91#include <sys/netmgr.h>
92#define apd_makedev(maj, min) makedev(ND_LOCAL_NODE, (maj), (min))
93#elif defined makedev
94/* There's a "makedev" macro. */
95#define apd_makedev(maj, min) makedev((maj), (min))
96#elif defined mkdev || ((defined _WIN32 || defined __WIN32__) && !defined(__CYGWIN__))
97/* Windows. <sigh> */
98#define apd_makedev(maj, min) mkdev((maj), (min))
99#else
100/* There's a "makedev" function. */
101#define apd_makedev(maj, min) makedev((maj), (min))
102#endif
103
104/* exported */
105dev_t
106pack_native(int n, unsigned long numbers[], const char **error)
107{
108 dev_t dev = 0;
109
110 if (n == 2) {
111 dev = apd_makedev(numbers[0], numbers[1]);
112 if ((unsigned long)major(dev) != numbers[0])
113 *error = iMajorError;
114 else if ((unsigned long)minor(dev) != numbers[1])
115 *error = iMinorError;
116 } else
117 *error = tooManyFields;
118 return (dev);
119}

139#define major_freebsd(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0x0000ff00) >> 8))
140#define minor_freebsd(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0xffff00ff) >> 0))
141#define makedev_freebsd(x,y) ((dev_t)((((x) << 8) & 0x0000ff00) | \
142 (((y) << 0) & 0xffff00ff)))

227#define major_8_24(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0xff000000) >> 24))
228#define minor_8_24(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0x00ffffff) >> 0))

248
249#define major_12_12_8(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0xfff00000) >> 20))
250#define unit_12_12_8(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0x000fff00) >> 8))
251#define subunit_12_12_8(x) ((int32_t)(((x) & 0x000000ff) >> 0))
252#define makedev_12_12_8(x,y,z) ((dev_t)((((x) << 20) & 0xfff00000) | \
253 (((y) << 8) & 0x000fff00) | \
254 (((z) << 0) & 0x000000ff)))
255
256static dev_t
257pack_bsdos(int n, unsigned long numbers[], const char **error)
258{
259 dev_t dev = 0;
260
261 if (n == 2) {
262 dev = makedev_12_20(numbers[0], numbers[1]);
263 if ((unsigned long)major_12_20(dev) != numbers[0])
264 *error = iMajorError;
265 if ((unsigned long)minor_12_20(dev) != numbers[1])
266 *error = iMinorError;
267 } else if (n == 3) {
268 dev = makedev_12_12_8(numbers[0], numbers[1], numbers[2]);
269 if ((unsigned long)major_12_12_8(dev) != numbers[0])
270 *error = iMajorError;
271 if ((unsigned long)unit_12_12_8(dev) != numbers[1])
272 *error = "invalid unit number";
273 if ((unsigned long)subunit_12_12_8(dev) != numbers[2])
274 *error = "invalid subunit number";
275 } else
276 *error = tooManyFields;
277 return (dev);
278}

281 /* list of formats and pack functions */
282 /* this list must be sorted lexically */
283static const struct format {
284 const char *name;
285 pack_t *pack;
286} formats[] = {
287 {"386bsd", pack_8_8},
288 {"4bsd", pack_8_8},
289 {"bsdos", pack_bsdos},
290 {"freebsd", pack_freebsd},
291 {"hpux", pack_8_24},
292 {"isc", pack_8_8},
293 {"linux", pack_8_8},
294 {"native", pack_native},
295 {"netbsd", pack_netbsd},
296 {"osf1", pack_12_20},
297 {"sco", pack_8_8},
298 {"solaris", pack_14_18},
299 {"sunos", pack_8_8},
300 {"svr3", pack_8_8},
301 {"svr4", pack_14_18},
302 {"ultrix", pack_8_8},
303};
304
305static int
306compare_format(const void *key, const void *element)
307{
308 const char *name;
309 const struct format *format;
310
311 name = key;
312 format = element;
313
314 return (strcmp(name, format->name));
315}
316
317
318pack_t *
319pack_find(const char *name)
320{
321 struct format *format;
322
323 format = bsearch(name, formats,
324 sizeof(formats)/sizeof(formats[0]),
325 sizeof(formats[0]), compare_format);
326 if (format == 0)
327 return (NULL);
328 return (format->pack);
329}
